%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5bdca5c9dde8674f991e13cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22671%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ERenaissance%20Technologies%20CEO%20Peter%20Brown%20discussed%20the%20hedge%20fund's%20investing%20and%20hiring%20approach.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBrown%20had%20the%20idea%20for%20IBM's%20%26quot%3BDeep%20Blue%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20spent%20over%202%2C000%20nights%20sleeping%20in%20his%20office.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ERenTech%20was%20founded%20by%20Jim%20Simons%2C%20a%20former%20MIT%20math%20professor%20and%20Cold%20War%20codebreaker.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20boss%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frenaissance-technologies-hedge-fund-bests-warren-buffett-10-biggest-holdings-2019-11%3Futm_medium%3Dingest%26r%3DUS%26IR%3DT%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%26utm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%26_gl%3D1*1xsf293*_ga*NjExMTk3OTM5LjE2ODIwNzA3NzY.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5NTEzNzk5Ny44Mi4xLjE2OTUxMzk3MDguNDYuMC4w%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20the%20most%20successful%20hedge%20funds%20in%20history%3C%2Fa%3E%20discussed%20his%20firm's%20approach%20to%20investing%20and%20hiring%20during%20a%20recent%20episode%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goldmansachs.com%2Fintelligence%2Fpodcasts%2Fepisodes%2F09-11-2023-peter-brown.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20Exchanges%3A%20Great%20Investors%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Brown%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20Renaissance%20Technologies%2C%20a%20quant%20fund%20founded%20by%20former%20Cold%20War%20codebreaker%20and%20MIT%20math%20professor%20Jim%20Simons.%20The%20firm's%20flagship%20Medallion%20fund%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-jim-simons-renaissance-technologies-has-outperformed-market-30-years-2019-12%5C%22%3Edelivered%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20gross%20annualized%20return%20of%2066%25%20between%201988%20and%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%20disclosed%20that%20IBM's%20%26quot%3BDeep%20Blue%26quot%3B%20supercomputer%20was%20his%20idea%2C%20he's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Frenaissance-technologies-hedge-fund-ceo-goldman-sachs-peter-brown-finance-2023-9%5C%22%3Espent%20more%20than%202%2C000%20nights%20sleeping%20in%20his%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20he%20once%20gave%20someone%20a%20raise%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%20to%20justify%20calling%20them%20so%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHere%20are%20Brown's%2011%20best%20quotes%2C%20lightly%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20idea%20that%20through%20mathematics%2C%20it%20might%20be%20possible%20to%20build%20machines%20that%20do%20what%20humans%20do.%20Whether%20it's%20speech%20recognition%2C%20machine%20translation%2C%20or%20building%20large%20language%20models%2C%20or%20chess%2C%20or%20making%20investment%20decisions%2C%20I%20continue%20to%20love%20the%20process%20of%20showing%20that%20human%20intelligence%2C%20intuition%2C%20creativity%2C%20and%20finesse%20are%20nothing%20more%20than%20computation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20%26quot%3BHe%20called%20me%20in%20my%20office%20and%20told%20me%20that%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20chess%20machine%2C%20he'd%20put%20up%20the%20million%20dollars.%20So%2C%20we%20did.%20Three%20friends%20from%20graduate%20school%20built%20the%20machine.%20I%20named%20it%20Deep%20Blue.%26quot%3B%20(Brown%20was%20recalling%20his%20role%20in%20creating%20IBM's%20famous%20supercomputer.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20%26quot%3BI%20took%20one%20look%20at%20our%20newborn%20daughter%20and%20realized%20I%20had%20no%20choice%20in%20the%20matter.%20The%20decision%20to%20leave%20computational%20linguistics%20for%20a%20small%20hedge%20fund%20that%20no%20one%20had%20ever%20heard%20of%20was%20made%20purely%20for%20financial%20reasons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20%26quot%3BUnbeknownst%20to%20my%20wife%2C%20I%20put%20our%20life%20savings%20into%20the%20company's%20funds%20as%20a%20way%20of%20motivating%20me%2C%20and%20set%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20%26quot%3BI%20went%20into%20Jim's%20office%20and%20told%20him%20that%20I'd%20screwed%20up%20in%20not%20appreciating%20the%20risk%20we%20were%20taking%2C%20and%20said%20that%20if%20he%20wanted%20me%20to%20resign%2C%20I%20would%20resign.%20But%20he%20responded%2C%20'Peter%2C%20quite%20the%20opposite.%20Now%20that%20you've%20been%20through%20such%20a%20stressful%20losing%20period%2C%20you're%20far%20more%20valuable%20to%20me%20and%20to%20the%20firm%20than%20you%20were%20before.'%20Now%2C%20that%20response%20really%20tells%20you%20something%20about%20Jim%20Simons.%26quot%3B%20(Brown%20was%20recalling%20the%20fallout%20from%20the%20dot-com%20crash.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20%26quot%3BProductivity-wise%2C%20it's%20really%20fantastic%20being%20able%20to%20spend%20nearly%2080%20straight%20hours%20each%20week%2C%20with%20no%20interruptions%20except%20sleep%2C%20thinking%20about%20work%2C%20before%20spending%20three%20more%20normal%20days%20at%20home.%20Of%20course%2C%20I%20really%20miss%20my%20family.%20But%20the%20freedom%20to%20concentrate%20non-stop%20on%20work%20while%20surrounded%20by%20my%20colleagues%20is%20hugely%20valuable.%20And%20the%20job%20is%20so%20demanding%2C%20I%20really%20don't%20see%20how%20I%20could%20do%20it%20otherwise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20around%201%20o'clock%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20and%20I%20picked%20up%20the%20phone%20to%20call%20him.%20And%20a%20colleague%20says%20to%20me%2C%20'Wait.%20You%20can't%20call%20this%20guy%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night.%20He%20doesn't%20make%20enough%20money.'%20So%2C%20I%20said%2C%20'Fine.%20How%20about%20this%3F%20I'll%20call%20him.%20I'll%20tell%20him%20we're%20going%20to%20give%20him%20a%20raise.%20And%20then%20ask%20him%20our%20question.'%20And%20so%2C%20that's%20what%20we%20did.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E8.%20%26quot%3BWe%20find%20it%20much%20easier%20to%20teach%20mathematicians%20about%20the%20markets%20than%20it%20is%20to%20teach%20mathematics%20and%20programming%20to%20people%20who%20know%20about%20the%20markets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E9.%20%26quot%3BOur%20Stony%20Brook%20office%20is%20chock-a-block%20full%20of%20highly%20accomplished%20physicists%2C%20mathematicians%2C%20and%20computer%20scientists.%20And%20our%20New%20York%20office%20is%20staffed%20with%20accountants%20and%20lawyers%20who%20make%20it%20clear%20to%20me%20every%20single%20day%20that%20scientists%20don't%20have%20a%20monopoly%20on%20brain%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E10.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20impose%20our%20own%20judgment%20on%20how%20the%20markets%20behave.%20We%20try%20to%20remember%20that%20we%20know%20how%20to%20build%20large%20mathematical%20models%2C%20and%20that's%20all%20we%20know.%20We%20don't%20know%20any%20economics.%20We%20don't%20have%20any%20insights%20in%20the%20markets.%20We%20just%20don't%20interfere%20with%20our%20trading%20systems.%26quot%3B%20(Brown%20noted%20that%20occasionally%20his%20team%20will%20intervene%20if%20something%20is%20going%20on%20in%20the%20world%20that%20the%20computers%20aren't%20factoring%20into%20their%20calculations.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E11.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20as%20for%20our%20secret%20sauce%2C%20of%20course%20there's%20nothing%20I'd%20rather%20do%20than%20disclose%20in%20great%20detail%20all%20the%20intellectual%20property%20that%20we've%20spent%20decades%20and%20billions%20of%20dollars%20creating.%20But%20I%20worry%20we%20don't%20have%20enough%20time%20for%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frenaissance-technologies-quant-fund-peter-brown-investing-hiring-ibm-sleep-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A16952