estors%20are%20jacking%20up%20rents%20and%20ripping%20off%20college%20students%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20house%20falling%20on%20top%20of%20a%20college%20student%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650a12f6bf943d00195bfbb4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBusiness%20is%20booming%20for%20investors%20in%20college%20housing%2C%20who%20poured%20%2422.9%20billion%20into%20the%20industry%20last%20year.%20But%20for%20students%2C%20the%20picture%20is%20more%20fraught.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWaterloo%2C%20a%2030-story%20tower%20just%20a%20few%20blocks%20west%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%2C%20has%20everything%20the%20modern%20college%20student%20needs%3A%20Its%20top%20floor%20features%20an%20infinity-edge%20pool%2C%20a%20pair%20of%20saunas%2C%20and%20a%20yoga%20studio%2C%20while%20the%20lobby%20includes%20an%20in-house%20coffee%20bar%20and%20ample%20nooks%20and%20tables%20for%20socializing%20or%20studying.%20To%20enjoy%20all%20this%2C%20a%20student%20just%20has%20to%20find%20five%20other%20friends%20willing%20to%20pony%20up%20a%20total%20of%20%248%2C100%20a%20month%20for%20a%20six-bed%2C%20six-bathroom%20apartment%2C%20or%20come%20up%20with%20as%20much%20as%20%241%2C900%20if%20they%20want%20their%20own%20studio.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20building%20isn't%20the%20only%20development%20turning%20college%20life%20into%20a%20luxury%20experience.%20In%20the%20decade-plus%20since%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis%2C%20the%20student-housing%20market%20has%20transformed%20from%20a%20patchwork%20of%20on-campus%20dorms%2C%20small%20apartments%2C%20and%20shared%20houses%20into%20a%20huge%20industry%20that's%20coveted%20by%20some%20of%20Wall%20Street's%20biggest%20investors.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20private-equity%20behemoth%20Blackstone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvestors-bet-on-student-housing-comeback-blackstone-tpg-2022-9%5C%22%3Epaid%20%2412.8%20billion%20to%20acquire%20American%20Campus%20Communities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20largest%20developer%20and%20manager%20of%20student%20housing%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20megadeal%20added%20nearly%20112%2C000%20beds%20to%20Blackstone's%20portfolio%20and%20helped%20drive%20a%20huge%20year%20for%20student-housing%20acquisitions%20%E2%80%94%20investors%20spent%20%2422.9%20billion%20in%20the%20space%2C%20more%20than%20double%20the%20sum%20in%202021%2C%20according%20to%20the%20commercial-real-estate%20firm%20CBRE.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20eye-popping%20numbers%20are%20part%20of%20a%20longer-term%20shift%20toward%20private%20college%20housing.%20Faced%20with%20pressure%20to%20grow%20their%20enrollments%2C%20and%20reluctant%20to%20take%20on%20debt%20for%20housing%20upgrades%2C%20more%20colleges%20and%20universities%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20have%20been%20striking%20deals%20known%20as%20public-private%20partnerships%2C%20in%20which%20they%20outsource%20the%20management%20of%20their%20residences%20to%20a%20third%20party.%20And%20a%20greater%20number%20of%20universities%20are%20simply%20banking%20on%20off-campus%20developers%20to%20absorb%20the%20spillover%20from%20overstuffed%20dorms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20schools%20%E2%80%94%20and%20investors%20eager%20to%20cash%20in%20on%20steady%20profits%20from%20student%20housing%20%E2%80%94%20this%20is%20a%20win-win.%20But%20for%20students%2C%20the%20picture%20is%20more%20fraught.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nmhc.org%2Fglobalassets%2Fresearch--insight%2Fresearch-reports%2Fstudent-housing%2F2023-research-foundation-affordability-in-purpose-built-student-housing.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Multifamily%20Housing%20Council%20found%20that%20rent%20for%20student%20housing%20jumped%2025%25%20between%202013%20and%202020%20when%20adjusting%20for%20inflation%2C%20which%20outpaced%20tuition%20hikes.%20Moody's%20Analytics%20recently%20warned%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Baffordability%20crisis%26quot%3B%20for%20college%20students%2C%20noting%20that%20since%202019%2C%20rents%20for%20student%20housing%20in%20a%20sample%20of%20notable%20college%20towns%20had%20grown%20faster%20than%20those%20of%20regular%20apartments.%20The%20start%20of%20the%202022%20academic%20year%20brought%20%26quot%3Bnever-before-seen%20rent%20growth%26quot%3B%20for%20student%20housing%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.realpage.com%2Fanalytics%2Fstudent-housing-outlook-for-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERealPage%20Market%20Analytics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20real-estate-software%20company%2C%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchools%20could%20step%20up%20to%20provide%20more%20housing%20themselves%2C%20but%20that's%20much%20easier%20said%20than%20done.%20Funding%20cutbacks%2C%20higher%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20local%20zoning%20laws%20make%20it%20difficult%20for%20in-demand%20colleges%20to%20get%20new%20housing%20off%20the%20ground.%20All%20this%20means%20heftier%20rent%20bills%20for%20students%20who%20are%20already%20navigating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-not-going-to-college-tuition-costs-higher-education-2023-9%5C%22%3Erising%20tuition%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-tuition-costs-too-much-make-degrees-matter-less-jobs-2023-9%5C%22%3Ecosts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-private-debt-no-relief-interest-rates-payments-2023-8%5C%22%3Egrowing%20mountain%20of%20student%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvan%20Scope%20Crafts%2C%20a%20fifth-year%20Ph.D.%20student%20at%20UT%20Austin%20who's%20seen%20the%20monthly%20rent%20for%20his%20off-campus%20studio%20apartment%20rise%20from%20roughly%20%24900%20to%20%241%2C300%20during%20his%20time%20at%20the%20school%2C%20framed%20the%20issue%20bluntly%3A%20%26quot%3BUniversity%20students%20are%20being%20thrown%20to%20the%20wolves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EStudent%20housing%20goes%20private%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gold%20rush%20in%20student%20housing%20is%20a%20relatively%20new%20phenomenon.%20Back%20in%20the%201980s%20and%20'90s%2C%20most%20college%20students%20either%20lived%20in%20bland%2C%20cinder-block-walled%20dorms%20or%20in%20conventional%20apartments%20farther%20from%20campus.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20the%20years%20surrounding%20the%20Great%20Recession%20that%20student%20housing%20experienced%20its%20%26quot%3Brenaissance%2C%26quot%3B%20Carl%20Whitaker%2C%20the%20director%20of%20research%20and%20analysis%20at%20RealPage%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20those%20tumultuous%20years%2C%20more%20people%20pursued%20degrees%20in%20hopes%20of%20catching%20a%20break%20in%20a%20tough%20job%20market.%20And%20all%20those%20students%20needed%20somewhere%20to%20live.%20What%20was%20once%20a%20niche%20endeavor%20now%20looked%20like%20a%20surefire%20bet.%20Companies%20such%20as%20American%20Campus%20Communities%20and%20Campus%20Apartments%20had%20also%20begun%20offering%20a%20model%20for%20privately%20owned%20student%20housing%3A%20fresh%2C%20gleaming%20properties%20conveniently%20near%20campus%2C%20with%20amenities%20including%20pools%2C%20gyms%2C%20and%20study%20lounges%20designed%20to%20lure%20students.%20The%20promise%20of%20recession-proof%20profits%20in%20a%20relatively%20untapped%20market%20spurred%20a%20construction%20boom%20%E2%80%94%20RealPage%20estimated%20that%20roughly%2080%25%20of%20privately%20owned%20student%20housing%20had%20been%20built%20in%20the%20past%2020%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20barista%20pours%20coffee%20at%20Waterloo's%20in-house%20coffee%20bar%2C%20which%20is%20decked%20out%20in%20shades%20of%20pink%20and%20blue%20punctuated%20by%20the%20greenery%20of%20indoor%20plants.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65089fd8f05aa00019be8643%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221326%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20in-house%20coffee%20bar%20on%20the%20ground%20floor%20of%20Waterloo%2C%20a%20new%20student-housing%20development%20near%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%3Cp%3EKristian%20Alveo%2C%20Provided%20by%20LV%20Collective%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20their%20own%20projects%2C%20private%20companies%20began%20signing%20more%20deals%20to%20manage%20and%20modernize%20on-campus%20housing%20for%20cash-strapped%20schools.%20Under%20this%20kind%20of%20arrangement%2C%20a%20school%20might%20lease%20campus%20land%20to%20a%20private%20developer%2C%20who%20would%20then%20build%20housing%20and%20profit%20off%20the%20rent%20payments.%20Or%20the%20school%20could%20choose%20to%20retain%20ownership%20of%20an%20existing%20dorm%20building%20but%20delegate%20the%20renovation%20and%20management%20to%20a%20company%20that%20would%20collect%20the%20rents.%20These%20arrangements%20allowed%20colleges%20to%20revamp%20their%20buildings%20without%20shouldering%20more%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStudent%20housing%20over%20the%202010s%20decade%20proved%20that%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20resilience%20and%20stability%20in%20the%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Whitaker%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20amenities%20arms%20race%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sudden%20popularity%20of%20private%20student%20housing%20also%20triggered%20a%20race%20among%20developers%20to%20add%20amenities%20that%20could%20be%20highlighted%20in%20advertising%20materials.%20Across%20the%20country%2C%20but%20particularly%20near%20in-demand%20schools%20in%20the%20South%2C%20companies%20sought%20to%20one-up%20each%20other%20with%20lavish%20perks.%20Since%20parents%20are%20often%20the%20ones%20footing%20the%20bill%2C%20Whitaker%20told%20me%2C%20many%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20more%20to%20ensure%20their%20children%20have%20access%20to%20the%20comforts%20and%20prime%20locations%20that%20these%20buildings%20offer.%20Today%2C%20the%20results%20look%20more%20like%20tastefully%20appointed%20resorts%20than%20what%20older%20generations%20may%20recognize%20as%20%26quot%3Bstudent%20housing.%26quot%3B%20Near%20UT%20Austin%2C%20a%20cluster%20of%20newly%20built%20high-rises%20in%20an%20area%20known%20as%20West%20Campus%20embodies%20this%20trend%20better%20than%20perhaps%20anywhere%20else%20in%20the%20nation.%20A%20few%20blocks%20from%20Waterloo%2C%20a%2019-story%20tower%20called%20Villas%20on%20Rio%20advertises%20%26quot%3Bvacation-style%20amenities%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20a%20full%20spa%20and%20a%20sky%20lounge%20with%20sweeping%20views%20of%20the%20city.%20Another%20building%2C%20The%20Mark%20Austin%2C%20includes%20a%20tanning%20bed%2C%20a%20two-story%20gym%2C%20and%20a%20bowling%20alley.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20rooftop%20pool%20at%20Waterloo%2C%20a%2030-story%20tower%20in%20Austin's%20West%20Campus%2C%20looks%20out%20over%20the%20city's%20skyline.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65089ce8f05aa00019be840e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223336%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20rooftop%20pool%20at%20Waterloo%20offers%20striking%20views%20of%20the%20Austin%20skyline.%3Cp%3EKristian%20Alveo%2C%20Provided%20by%20LV%20Collective%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Willson%2C%20a%20senior%20at%20UT%2C%20started%20his%20college%20career%20living%20in%20an%20on-campus%20dorm%20before%20moving%20to%20Villas%20on%20Rio%20for%20a%20year.%20To%20keep%20the%20cost%20manageable%2C%20Willson%20told%20me%2C%20he%20split%20a%20two-bedroom%20unit%20among%20four%20people%20and%20generally%20cooked%20meals%20at%20home.%20Even%20with%20his%20frugality%2C%20he%20came%20to%20realize%20that%20the%20prices%20in%20West%20Campus%20were%20%26quot%3Bimpossible%20to%20rationalize%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20college%20student.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20coming%20from%20an%20on-campus%20dorm%2C%20then%2C%20obviously%2C%20they're%20a%20bit%20of%20an%20enhancement%20to%20your%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20Willson%20said%20of%20the%20off-campus%20amenities.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20wow%2C%20this%20is%20such%20a%20fun%2C%20cool%20upgrade.'%20But%20the%20novelty%20wears%20off%20really%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20top-tier%20universities%20need%20more%20housing%20to%20match%20the%20pressure%20to%20grow%20their%20enrollments%20and%20rein%20in%20costs%20for%20students.%20But%20critics%20of%20these%20upscale%20developments%20say%20they%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhechingerreport.org%2Fluxury-private-student-housing-further-divides-rich-and-poor-on-campuses%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereinforce%20the%20divide%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20wealthy%20and%20poor%20students.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20increasingly%20two%20UTs%2C%26quot%3B%20Scope%20Crafts%2C%20the%20Ph.D.%20student%2C%20told%20me%20%E2%80%94%20one%20for%20students%20whose%20families%20can%20afford%20to%20shell%20out%20the%20money%20for%20housing%20in%20areas%20like%20West%20Campus%2C%20and%20another%20for%20those%20who%20are%20forced%20to%20live%20in%20cheaper%20housing%20far%20away%20from%20the%20classrooms.%20%26quot%3BThe%20experience%20couldn't%20be%20more%20dramatically%20different%20between%20these%20two%20classes%20of%20students.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGina%20Cowart%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20American%20Campus%20Communities%2C%20which%20owns%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20apartment%20buildings%20in%20West%20Campus%2C%20told%20me%20in%20an%20email%20that%20%26quot%3Bultimately%2C%20affordability%20challenges%20result%20from%20not%20enough%20supply.%26quot%3B%20When%20asked%20about%20the%20cost%20pressures%20on%20college%20students%2C%20Cowart%20said%20the%20company%20offers%20%26quot%3Ba%20variety%20of%20unit-types%20and%20price%20points%20so%20that%20students%20of%20varying%20financial%20backgrounds%20have%20access%20to%20academically-oriented%20communities.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20overwhelming%20need%20for%20cheaper%20housing%20has%20prompted%20cities%2C%20including%20Austin%2C%20to%20get%20creative.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20changes%20to%20the%20zoning%20code%20in%202019%2C%20developers%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20West%20Campus%20can%20now%20build%20as%20high%20as%2030%20stories%20%E2%80%94%20an%20increase%20of%20125%20feet%20%E2%80%94%20in%20exchange%20for%20dedicating%2020%25%20of%20the%20units%20to%20affordable%20housing.%20The%20first%20tower%20to%20reach%20that%20new%20limit%20was%20Waterloo%2C%20which%20opened%20last%20year.%20Half%20of%20the%20affordable%20units%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20studios%2C%20rent%20for%20%241%2C095%20a%20month%3B%20the%20other%20half%20go%20for%20%24818.%20They're%20indistinguishable%20from%20the%20other%20apartments%2C%20and%20students%20who%20rely%20on%20financial%20aid%20can%20apply%20for%20one%20of%20the%20units%20and%20get%20access%20to%20all%20the%20building's%20amenities%2C%20while%20paying%20significantly%20less%20than%20the%20going%20rate%20for%20a%20similar%20unit%20in%20downtown%20Austin.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWaterloo%20is%20the%20work%20of%20LV%20Collective%2C%20an%20Austin%20development%20firm%20that%20has%20been%20instrumental%20in%20reshaping%20West%20Campus.%20On%20a%20recent%20Friday%20morning%2C%20I%20met%20the%20company's%20CEO%2C%20David%20Kanne%2C%20in%20the%20building's%20sun-drenched%20lobby%2C%20which%20was%20decked%20out%20in%20floral%20wallpapers%20and%20Instagram-friendly%20pastels.%20It%20felt%20a%20little%20like%20a%20hotel%20from%20the%20HBO%20hit%20show%20%26quot%3BThe%20White%20Lotus%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20if%20the%20series'%20guests%20needed%20to%20squeeze%20in%20late-night%20study%20sessions%20after%20lounging%20at%20the%20pool.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tables%20on%20the%20ground%20floor%20of%20Waterloo%20are%20lined%20on%20both%20sides%20by%20arched%20nooks%20for%20additional%20study%20spaces%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6508a194cd637c0019c73fa7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221171%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20ground%20floor%20of%20Waterloo%20also%20features%20ample%20seating%20for%20studying%20or%20socializing.%3Cp%3EKristian%20Alveo%2C%20provided%20by%20LV%20Collective%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EKanne%2C%20who%20was%20a%20vocal%20advocate%20for%20the%202019%20zoning%20changes%2C%20told%20me%20he%20believed%20greater%20housing%20density%20near%20campus%20was%20key%20to%20making%20rents%20more%20affordable%20for%20students.%20Basically%2C%20he%20argues%20that%20cities%20should%20relax%20height%20restrictions%20and%20other%20zoning%20rules%20and%20allow%20developers%20to%20squeeze%20more%20units%20into%20a%20single%20parcel%20of%20land%2C%20as%20long%20as%20they%20agree%20to%20add%20some%20income-restricted%20apartments%20into%20the%20mix.%20Kanne%20pointed%20out%20that%20because%20of%20all%20the%20new%20construction%20in%20West%20Campus%2C%20rents%20in%20the%20area%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthedailytexan.com%2F2022%2F11%2F18%2Fas-prices-to-live-in-west-campus-keep-rises-students-seek-relief%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSince%25202020%252C%2520West%2520Campus%2520rent%2Ca%2520price%2520increase%2520of%252027%2525.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erisen%20at%20a%20slower%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20in%20Austin%20as%20a%20whole.%20He%20said%20his%20company%20was%20working%20with%20local%20governments%20in%20other%20cities%20where%20it's%20building%20projects%2C%20including%20Gainesville%2C%20Florida%2C%20and%20Ann%20Arbor%2C%20Michigan%2C%20to%20apply%20the%20lessons%20from%20West%20Campus.%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20today's%20world%2C%20where%20construction%20prices%20have%20escalated%20and%20costs%20are%20going%20up%20across%20the%20board%2C%20you%20have%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20be%20more%20thoughtful%2C%20more%20intentional%2C%20with%20the%20spaces%20you%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Kanne%20told%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECity%20governments%20can%20push%20for%20only%20so%20much%20from%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20however.%20In%20some%20parts%20of%20Austin%2C%20including%20West%20Campus%2C%20a%20developer%20can%20still%20get%20a%20density%20bonus%20by%20paying%20a%20fee%20rather%20than%20actually%20delivering%20affordable%20units.%20And%20even%20the%20affordable%20units%20that%20do%20get%20built%20may%20not%20be%20enough%20to%20make%20a%20significant%20dent%20in%20overall%20prices.%20Waterloo%20is%20devoting%2020%25%20of%20its%20units%20to%20affordable%20housing%2C%20but%20because%20they're%20all%20studios%2C%20that%20translates%20to%20only%2049%20beds%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20796%20in%20the%20building%20%E2%80%94%20or%20roughly%206%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EStudents%20get%20the%20short%20end%20of%20the%20stick%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20in%20student%20housing%20have%20enjoyed%20boom%20times%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%20But%20for%20many%20students%2C%20the%20barriers%20to%20securing%20affordable%20housing%20have%20continued%20to%20mount.%20Even%20those%20seeking%20cheaper%20prices%20farther%20away%20from%20campus%20haven't%20seen%20much%20relief%3A%20Between%202013%20and%202020%2C%20rents%20at%20conventional%20apartments%20within%203%20miles%20of%20college%20campuses%20grew%2030%25%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20the%20National%20Multifamily%20Housing%20Council%2C%20which%20blamed%20the%20surge%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bsevere%20undersupply%20of%20housing%20of%20all%20types%20and%20at%20all%20price%20points.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMuch%20of%20the%20rent%20increases%20in%20purpose-built%20student%20housing%20result%20from%20students%20competing%20with%20other%20residents%20for%20a%20limited%20housing%20supply%20in%20markets%20where%20housing%20prices%20are%20already%20increasing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoody's%20Analytics%20similarly%20looked%20at%2011%20metros%20in%20which%20college%20students%20accounted%20for%20more%20than%2019%25%20of%20the%20total%20population%20and%20found%20that%20rents%20at%20student-housing%20properties%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcre.moodysanalytics.com%2Finsights%2Fcre-news%2Faffordability-crisis-comes-for-college-students%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrew%20about%203%25%20faster%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%20average%2C%20than%20at%20regular%20apartments%20over%20the%20past%20four%20years.%20Of%20the%20seven%20metros%20in%20which%20student-housing%20rent%20growth%20exceeded%20that%20of%20regular%20apartments%2C%20State%20College%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20saw%20the%20widest%20gap%2C%20at%2015%20percentage%20points.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETight%20housing%20supply%2C%20combined%20with%20resilient%20demand%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20%26quot%3Bquite%20an%20increase%26quot%3B%20in%20rents%20for%20many%20students%2C%20Lu%20Chen%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20Moody's%20Analytics%2C%20told%20me.%20And%20prices%20are%20still%20climbing%3A%20For%20fall%202023%2C%20year-over-year%20rent%20growth%20for%20privately%20owned%20student%20housing%20reached%208.6%25%20when%20averaged%20across%20the%20leasing%20season%2C%20RealPage%20found.%20While%20student%20housing%20is%20often%20cheaper%20than%20market-rate%20rentals%20on%20an%20absolute%20basis%2C%20%26quot%3Bneither%20option%20is%20a%20particular%20safe%20haven%20as%20housing%20affordability%20issues%20persist%20across%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20Moody's%20report%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fn3fAA%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Year-over-year%20change%20in%20effective%20asking%20rents%20for%20off-campus%20student%20housing%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ETotal%20college%20enrollment%20has%20been%20on%20the%20decline%20across%20the%20country%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20which%20could%20put%20pressure%20on%20student-housing%20rents%20to%20fall%20at%20some%20schools.%20But%20the%20picture%20is%20mixed%3A%20In-demand%2C%20selective%20universities%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insidehighered.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2F10%2F17%2Fenrollment-trends-new-and-old-emerge-pandemic%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinuing%20to%20expand%20their%20student%20bodies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20squeezed%20the%20availability%20of%20school-owned%20beds.%20While%20total%20US%20enrollment%20dropped%206.5%25%20between%20fall%202017%20and%20fall%202021%2C%20enrollment%20at%20Power%20Five%20schools%20%E2%80%94%20those%20that%20belong%20to%20the%20five%20largest%20athletics%20conferences%20%E2%80%94%20rose%205.2%25%20in%20the%20same%20time%20span%2C%20according%20to%20RealPage.%20Highly%20selective%2C%20non-Power%20Five%20schools%20are%20also%20reporting%20increases.%20Facing%20a%20shortage%20of%20on-campus%20housing%2C%20Middlebury%20College%20said%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Falexperry%2F2023%2F08%2F20%2Fno-room-at-the-dorm-as-college-begins-some-students-are-scrambling-for-housing%2F%3Fsh%3D34df14431f59%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epay%20some%20students%20%2410%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20take%20the%20fall%20semester%20off.%20The%20University%20of%20Tennessee%2C%20Knoxville%2C%20last%20year%20was%20forced%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wbir.com%2Farticle%2Fnews%2Feducation%2Futk-student-housing-solutions%2F51-c1c07e0f-b47c-4ac4-ab26-857c1ab6063b%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elease%20out%20rooms%20at%20a%20hotel%206%20miles%20off%20campus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20nearly%20450%20students%20at%20Arizona%20State%20University%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc15.com%2Fnews%2Flocal-news%2Fnearly-450-students-living-in-hotels-as-asu-dorms-full%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarted%20last%20fall's%20semester%20in%20hotels%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20the%20overflow%20from%20campus.%20Both%20state%20schools%20reported%20record%20enrollments%20last%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDRJfL%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Occupancy%20rates%20of%20off-campus%20student%20housing%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20ease%20this%20burden%2C%20more%20schools%20are%20relying%20on%20partnerships%20with%20private%20developers%20instead%20of%20taking%20on%20debt%20to%20build%20fully%20owned%20housing.%20Public-private%20partnerships%20can%20be%20effective%20in%20producing%20housing%20but%20%26quot%3Bmay%20pose%20challenges%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20%3Cem%3Eaffordable%3C%2Fem%3E%20student%20housing%20because%20the%20private%20entity's%20focus%20is%20on%20profits%20over%20serving%20students%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhousingmatters.urban.org%2Farticles%2Fcolleges-and-universities-are-experiencing-their-own-affordable-housing-crisis%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPublic%252Dprivate%2520partnerships%2520can%2520be%2Cexpand%2520housing%2520options%2520off%2520campus.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Urban%20Institute%20said.%20The%20profit-driven%20goals%20of%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20while%20not%20inherently%20bad%2C%20differ%20from%20the%20accessibility-focused%20priorities%20of%20public%20institutions%2C%20Donald%20Cohen%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20executive%20director%20of%20In%20the%20Public%20Interest%20and%20a%20coauthor%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Privatization%20of%20Everything%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20just%20different%20interests%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20times%20when%20those%20interests%20may%20be%20in%20line%2C%20or%20they%20may%20be%20kind%20of%20in%20line%2C%20or%20they%20may%20conflict.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThis%20is%20just%20the%20beginning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20may%20be%20some%20short-term%20relief%20coming%20for%20students%2C%20however.%20Whitaker%20told%20me%20he%20expected%20rent%20growth%20to%20come%20down%20for%20fall%202024%2C%20to%20between%202.5%25%20and%203%25%2C%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-decline-fall-apartment-housing-market-landlords-tenant-lease-construction-2023-3%5C%22%3Ebroader%20apartment%20market%20cooled%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Compared%20with%20this%20year%2C%20when%20year-over-year%20rent%20increases%20for%20student%20housing%20surpassed%208%25%2C%20that's%20a%20pretty%20significant%20drop.%20Still%2C%20that%20growth%20rate%20would%20be%20a%20little%20higher%20than%20pre-pandemic%20norms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELonger%20term%2C%20there's%20no%20swell%20of%20student-housing%20construction%20on%20the%20horizon%20that%20could%20push%20rents%20down%20much%20further.%20While%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-decline-fall-apartment-housing-market-landlords-tenant-lease-construction-2023-3%5C%22%3Ehistoric%20number%20of%20apartment%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20underway%20across%20the%20country%2C%20%26quot%3Bstudent%20housing%20isn't%20adding%20as%20much%20new%20supply%20as%20the%20conventional%20marketplace%2C%26quot%3B%20Whitaker%20told%20me.%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20high-value%20sites%20near%20campuses%20have%20already%20been%20built%20on%2C%20and%20construction%20financing%20is%20harder%20to%20come%20by.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FhufL3%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Number%20of%20beds%20delivered%20for%20off-campus%20student%20housing%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20supply%20and%20demand%20can%20differ%20starkly%20from%20campus%20to%20campus.%20Investors%20have%20shown%20particular%20interest%20in%20building%20and%20acquiring%20properties%20near%20Power%20Five%20schools%20and%20other%20top%20research%20institutions%20in%20the%20South%20and%20Southeast%2C%20where%20enrollments%20are%20growing%20and%20demographic%20trends%20bode%20well%20for%20occupancy%20and%20rent%20growth%2C%20Graham%20Sowden%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20officer%20of%20the%20real-estate%20firm%20RREAF%20Holdings%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email.%20That%20means%20institutions%20such%20as%20UT%20Austin%2C%20which%20last%20year%20welcomed%20its%20largest-ever%20student%20body%2C%20can't%20afford%20to%20sit%20idle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Allen%2C%20the%20university's%20executive%20director%20for%20real-estate%20finance%20and%20asset%20management%2C%20told%20me%20the%20school%20recognized%20the%20value%20of%20living%20near%20campus%3A%20Students%20who%20live%20closer%20to%20classes%20tend%20to%20have%20higher%20GPAs%20and%20graduation%20rates%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20better%20overall%20college%20experience.%20With%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20UT%20Austin%20has%20acquired%20two%20off-campus%20apartment%20properties%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%20and%20is%20redeveloping%20one%20of%20its%20dorms%20through%20a%20public-private%20partnership%2C%20which%20is%20set%20to%20add%20roughly%20400%20beds.%20Nearly%201%2C400%20beds%20for%20graduate%20students%20are%20planned%20east%20of%20campus%2C%20across%20a%20highway.%20Beyond%20that%2C%20a%20working%20group%20has%20identified%20other%20sites%20on%20campus%20where%20the%20school%20could%20add%20another%203%2C500%20beds%20over%20the%20next%20five%20to%20eight%20years%2C%20Allen%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAffordability%20of%20housing%20was%20an%20advantage%20for%20Austin%20years%20ago.%20It's%20a%20problem%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Allen%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe%20see%20the%20problem.%20We%20see%20the%20impact.%20And%20we're%20now%20fully%20focused%20on%2C%20'What%20are%20the%20tools%20at%20our%20disposal%20to%20help%20solve%20for%20affordability%2C%20to%20bring%20our%20students%20closer%20to%20campus%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-tuition-costs-too-much-make-degrees-matter-less-jobs-2023-9%5C%22%3Ebroader%20trends%3C%2Fa%3E%20squeezing%20students'%20wallets%20and%20pushing%20colleges%20toward%20privatization%20aren't%20going%20away.%20Student%20housing%20is%20no%20longer%20just%20a%20niche%20sector%20%E2%80%94%20the%20past%20few%20years%20have%20proved%20that%20investors%20are%20willing%20to%20bet%20big%20on%20the%20dorms%20of%20the%20future.%20The%20success%20of%20the%20industry%20has%20done%20little%20to%20ease%20the%20burdens%20for%20students%2C%20however.%20Unless%20schools%20find%20a%20way%20to%20come%20up%20with%20more%20housing%20at%20reasonable%20prices%2C%20students%20will%20be%20left%20searching%20for%20a%20lifeline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20the%20university%20has%20a%20responsibility%20to%20provide%20housing%20for%20its%20students%2C%20point%20blank%2C%26quot%3B%20Scope%20Crafts%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20didn't%20really%20feel%20like%20that%20obligation%20was%20being%20met.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%223c8b97546e40aba1336062912e763a0d%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics