%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2309.03409%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20September%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20study%20aimed%20to%20see%20how%20simple%20prompts%20could%20improve%20the%20performance%20of%20large%20language%20models%2C%20like%20ChatGPT's%20GPT-4%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-how-big-tech-will-win-again-2023-5%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20PaLM%202%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20is%20not%20clear%20how%20many%20prompts%20were%20used%20during%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20prompted%20with%20the%20phrase%2C%20researchers%20found%20that%20Google's%20PaLM%202%20model%20was%2080%25%20accurate%20while%20responding%20to%20a%20set%20of%20grade%20school%20math%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20creators%20of%20the%20over%208%2C500%20math%20problems%20used%20in%20the%20study%20wrote%20that%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpaperswithcode.com%2Fdataset%2Fgsm8k%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpaperswithcode.com%2Fdataset%2Fgsm8k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bbright%20middle%20school%20student%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20be%20able%20to%20solve%20all%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20prompt%2C%20the%20model%20was%20merely%2034%25%20accurate%20in%20answering%20the%20math%20problems%2C%20per%20the%20study.%20Meanwhile%2C%20prompting%20the%20AI%20with%20%26quot%3Blet's%20think%20step%20by%20step%26quot%3B%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20accuracy%20to%2071%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20automated%20the%20process%20of%20testing%20a%20large%20number%20of%20different%20phrases%20with%20a%20variety%20of%20AI%20models%20to%20understand%20which%20prompts%20would%20work%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20add%20context%20to%20these%20findings%2C%20a%202022%20joint%20study%20by%C2%A0researchers%C2%A0at%20Google%20and%C2%A0the%20University%20of%20Tokyo%C2%A0found%20that%20getting%20large%20language%20models%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2205.11916%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2205.11916%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bthink%20step%20by%20step%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20improved%20their%20accuracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatGPT's%20launch%20in%20November%20has%20sparked%20curiosity%20over%20how%20we%20should%20be%20speaking%20to%20AI%20to%C2%A0get%20the%20outcomes%20we%20desire.%20Some%20companies%20are%20even%20hiring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprompt-engineering-ai-chatgpt-jobs-explained-2023-3%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bprompt%20engineers%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0who%20specialize%20in%20crafting%20questions%20and%20phrases%20for%20AI%20to%20improve%20its%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnna%20Bernstein%2C%20a%20prompt%20engineer%20working%20for%20AI%20company%20Copy.ai%2C%20told%20Insider%20in%20August%20that%20to%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20the%C2%A0prompts%2C%20one%20should%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-write-better-ai-chatgpt-prompts-according-prompt-engineer-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euse%20a%20thesaurus%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20pay%20closer%20attention%20to%C2%A0verbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20groups%20have%20even%20put%20together%20%26quot%3Bprompt%20libraries%26quot%3B%20to%20share%20phrases%20to%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20like%20OpenAI's%20Discord%20community%2C%20where%20developers%20share%20sample%20phrases%20to%20get%20ChatGPT%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-channel-users-sharing-gpt-gpt4-chatgpt-prompts-jobs-languages-2023-5%5C%22%3Ehelp%20with%20job%20interviews%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20and%20the%20study's%20authors%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider%2C%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-google-researchers-deepmind-tell-take-deep-breath-improve-accuracy-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695201531000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63822274b4cf0100187d9a44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-google-researchers-deepmind-tell-take-deep-breath-improve-accuracy-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20the%20phrase%20was%20used%2C%20Google's%20PaLM%202%20AI%20model%20was%2080%25%20accurate%20with%20a%20set%20of%20grade%20school%20math%20problems%2C%20compared%20to%2034%25%20without%20it%2C%20per%20a%20study.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kteo%40insider.com%20(Kai%20Xiang%20Teo)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-google-researchers-deepmind-tell-take-deep-breath-improve-accuracy-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Women's%20Reservation%20Bill%3A%20The%20Issues%20to%20Consider%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2073rd%20and%2074th%20Amendments%20passed%20in%201993%2C%20which%20introduced%20panchayats%20and%20municipalities%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20reserve%20one-third%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20these%20bodies.%20The%20Constitution%20also%20provides%20for%20reservation%20of%20seats%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SCs)%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(STs)%20in%20proportion%20to%20their%20number%20in%20the%20population.%20The%20Constitution%20does%20not%20provide%20for%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies.%20Some%20members%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20had%20opposed%20reserving%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20legislatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E15%25%20of%20the%20total%20members%20of%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%20are%20women%20while%20in%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20women%20on%20average%20constitute%209%25%20of%20the%20total%20members.%20In%202015%2C%20the%20Report%20on%20the%20Status%20of%20Women%20in%20India%20noted%20that%20the%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20state%20assemblies%20and%20Parliament%20continues%20to%20be%20dismal.%20It%20noted%20that%20decision%20making%20positions%20in%20political%20parties%20have%20negligible%20presence%20of%20women.%20It%20recommended%20reserving%20at%20least%2050%25%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20local%20bodies%2C%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20Parliament%2C%20ministerial%20levels%2C%20and%20all%20decision-making%20bodies%20of%20the%20government.6%20The%20National%20Policy%20for%20the%20Empowerment%20of%20Women%20(2001)%20had%20stated%20that%20reservation%20will%20be%20considered%20in%20higher%20legislative%20bodies.7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBills%20amending%20the%20Constitution%20to%20reserve%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20Parliament%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20have%20been%20introduced%20in%201996%2C%201998%2C%201999%2C%20and%202008.%20The%20first%20three%20Bills%20lapsed%20with%20dissolution%20of%20their%20respective%20Lok%20Sabhas.%20The%202008%20Bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20and%20passed%20by%20Rajya%20Sabha%20but%20it%20also%20lapsed%20with%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%2014th%20Lok%20Sabha.%20The%201996%20Bill%20had%20been%20examined%20by%20a%20Joint%20Committee%20of%20Parliament%2C%20while%20the%202008%20Bill%20was%20examined%20by%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Personnel%2C%20Public%20Grievances%2C%20Law%20and%20Justice.%20Both%20Committees%20agreed%20with%20the%20proposal%20to%20reserve%20seats%20for%20women.%20Some%20of%20the%20recommendations%20given%20by%20the%20Committees%20include%3A%20(i)%20considering%20reservation%20for%20women%20belonging%20to%20other%20backward%20classes%20at%20an%20appropriate%20time%2C%20(ii)%20providing%20reservation%20for%20a%20period%20of%2015%20years%20and%20reviewing%20it%20thereafter%2C%20and%20(iii)%20working%20out%20the%20modalities%20to%20reserve%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20councils.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20(One%20Hundred%20and%20Twenty-Eighth%20Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%20was%20introduced%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20September%2019%2C%202023.%20The%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20reserve%20one-third%20of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20for%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20features%20of%20the%20Bill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%96%AA%20Reservation%20for%20women%3A%20The%20Bill%20reserves%2C%20as%20nearly%20as%20may%20be%2C%20one-third%20of%20all%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20and%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20of%20the%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi.%20This%20will%20also%20apply%20to%20the%20seats%20reserved%20for%20SCs%20and%20STs%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20states%20legislatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%96%AA%20Commencement%20of%20reservation%3A%20The%20reservation%20will%20be%20effective%20after%20the%20census%20conducted%20after%20the%20commencement%20of%20this%20Bill%20has%20been%20published.%20Based%20on%20the%20census%2C%20delimitation%20will%20be%20undertaken%20to%20reserve%20seats%20for%20women.%20The%20reservation%20will%20be%20provided%20for%20a%20period%20of%2015%20years.%20However%2C%20it%20shall%20continue%20till%20such%20date%20as%20determined%20by%20a%20law%20made%20by%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%96%AA%20Rotation%20of%20seats%3A%20Seats%20reserved%20for%20women%20will%20be%20rotated%20after%20each%20delimitation%2C%20as%20determined%20by%20a%20law%20made%20by%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIssues%20to%20consider%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20legislatures%20can%20be%20examined%20from%20three%20perspectives%3A%20(i)%20whether%20the%20policy%20of%20reservation%20for%20women%20can%20act%20as%20an%20effective%20instrument%20for%20their%20empowerment%2C%20(ii)%20whether%20alternate%20methods%20of%20increasing%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20legislatures%20are%20feasible%2C%20and%20(iii)%20whether%20there%20are%20any%20issues%20with%20the%20proposed%20method%20for%20reservation%20in%20the%20Bill.%20The%20analysis%20in%20this%20section%20is%20largely%20based%20on%20our%20earlier%20Brief%20published%20on%20the%202008%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPurpose%20of%20reservation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20group%20is%20not%20represented%20proportionately%20in%20the%20political%20system%2C%20its%20ability%20to%20influence%20policy-making%20is%20limited.%20The%20Convention%20on%20the%20Elimination%20of%20All%20Forms%20of%20Discrimination%20Against%20Women%20provides%20that%20discrimination%20against%20women%20must%20be%20eliminated%20in%20political%20and%20public%20life.%20While%20India%20is%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20Convention%2C%20discrimination%20in%20matters%20of%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20decision-making%20bodies%20has%20continued.%20The%20number%20of%20women%20MPs%20has%20increased%20from%205%25%20in%20the%20first%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%2015%25%20in%20the%2017th%20Lok%20Sabha%3B%20but%20the%20number%20continues%20to%20be%20quite%20low.%20A%202003%20study%20about%20the%20effect%20of%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20panchayats%20showed%20that%20women%20elected%20under%20the%20reservation%20policy%20invest%20more%20in%20the%20public%20goods%20closely%20linked%20to%20women%E2%80%99s%20concerns.%20The%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Personnel%2C%20Public%20Grievances%2C%20Law%20and%20Justice%20(2009)%20had%20noted%20that%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20local%20bodies%20has%20enabled%20them%20to%20make%20meaningful%20contributions.%20It%20also%20noted%20that%20concerns%20regarding%20women%20being%20proxies%20to%20men%20in%20local%20bodies%20have%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20baseless.%20The%20Inter-Parliamentary%20Union%20(2022)%20has%20noted%20that%20legislated%20quotas%20have%20been%20a%20decisive%20factor%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20representation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOpponents%20of%20the%20reservation%20policy%20argue%20that%20separate%20constituencies%20for%20women%20would%20not%20only%20narrow%20their%20outlook%20but%20lead%20to%20perpetuation%20of%20unequal%20status%20because%20they%20would%20be%20seen%20as%20not%20competing%20on%20merit.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20Renuka%20Ray%20argued%20against%20reserving%20seats%20for%20women%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20there%20is%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%2C%20the%20question%20of%20their%20consideration%20for%20general%20seats%2C%20however%20competent%20they%20may%20be%2C%20does%20not%20usually%20arise.%20We%20feel%20that%20women%20will%20get%20more%20chances%20if%20the%20consideration%20is%20of%20ability%20alone.%E2%80%9D%20Opponents%20also%20argue%20that%20reservation%20would%20not%20lead%20to%20political%20empowerment%20of%20women%20because%20larger%20issues%20of%20electoral%20reforms%20such%20as%20measures%20to%20check%20criminalisation%20of%20politics%2C%20internal%20democracy%20in%20political%20parties%2C%20and%20influence%20of%20black%20money%20have%20not%20been%20addressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlternate%20methods%20of%20representation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReservation%20of%20one-third%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20Parliament%20would%20restrict%20the%20choice%20of%20voters%20in%20the%20reserved%20constituencies.%20Two%20alternatives%20have%20been%20suggested%20by%20some%20experts%3A%20reservation%20for%20candidates%20within%20political%20parties%20(as%20some%20countries%20do%2C%20see%20Table%201)%3B%20and%20dual%20member%20constituencies%20where%20some%20constituencies%20shall%20have%20two%20candidates%2C%20one%20being%20a%20woman%20(see%20Table%202).%20Initially%2C%20India%20had%20multi-member%20constituencies%20which%20included%20an%20SC%2FST%20member.%20A%201961%20Act%20converted%20all%20constituencies%20into%20single%20member%20constituencies.%20The%20reasoning%20was%20that%20the%20constituencies%20were%20too%20large%20and%20SC%2FST%20members%20felt%20that%20they%20would%20gain%20in%20importance%20in%20single-%20member%20reserved%20constituencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131512%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.14.53-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22634%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131512%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.14.53-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131512%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.14.53-PM-300x195.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131512%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.14.53-PM-1024x664.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673890%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22411%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131622%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.16.11-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22725%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131622%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.16.11-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131622%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.16.11-PM-300x126.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20131622%2FScreenshot-2023-09-20-at-1.16.11-PM-1024x430.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673891%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22304%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%203%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERotating%20constituencies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%203%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20states%20that%20reserved%20seats%20shall%20be%20allotted%20by%20rotation%20after%20every%20delimitation%20exercise.%20This%20implies%20rotation%20approximately%20every%2010%20years%20as%20after%202026%20delimitation%20is%20mandated%20to%20take%20place%20after%20every%20census.%20Rotation%20of%20reserved%20seats%20may%20reduce%20the%20incentive%20for%20MPs%20to%20work%20for%20their%20constituencies%20as%20they%20could%20be%20ineligible%20to%20seek%20re-election%20from%20that%20constituency.%20A%20study%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Panchayati%20Raj%20recommended%20that%20rotation%20of%20constituencies%20should%20be%20discontinued%20at%20the%20panchayat%20level%20because%20almost%2085%25%20women%20were%20first-timers%20and%20only%2015%25%20women%20could%20get%20re-elected%20because%20the%20seats%20they%20were%20elected%20from%20were%20de-reserved.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20changes%20between%202008%20and%202023%20Bills%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20table%20below%20captures%20certain%20key%20changes%20between%20the%202008%20Bill%20as%20passed%20by%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20the%20Bill%20introduced%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp