%20the%20knowledge%20gives%20you%20the%20confidence%20to%20do%20the%20right%20thing%20in%20any%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDuring%20my%20classes%2C%20I%20emphasize%2C%20'It's%20not%20your%20fault%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20these%20things'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20come%20from%20a%20working-class%20background%20in%20Preston%2C%20England.%20I%20remember%20while%20I%20was%20doing%20my%20A-levels%2C%20my%20mum%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BJayne%2C%20can't%20you%20just%20leave%20school%20and%20go%20and%20get%20a%20job%20and%20bring%20some%20money%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20was%20motivated%20to%20get%20out%20of%20my%20situation.%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20horrible%20childhood%20%E2%80%94%20I%20just%20didn't%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20my%20hometown%20my%20whole%20life.%20I%20had%20an%20affinity%20for%20languages%20and%20wanted%20to%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20very%20entrepreneurial%20friend%2C%20and%20he%20credits%20that%20to%20his%20upper-middle-class%20background%20and%20business%20conversations%20at%20the%20dinner%20table.%20For%20me%2C%20at%20tea%2C%20I%20barely%20remember%20my%20father%20being%20there.%20But%20if%20he%20was%2C%20he%20would%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BDid%20you%20do%20your%20homework%3F%20All%20right%2C%20you%20can%20watch%20TV%20for%20half%20an%20hour.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20at%20Cambridge%20University%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-dining-etiquette-rules-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20silverware%2C%20you%20start%20on%20the%20outside%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20not%20to%20talk%20with%20my%20mouth%20full%20%E2%80%94but%20that's%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20overwhelmed%20in%20settings%20such%20as%20our%20dining%20hall%2C%20which%20was%20very%20%26quot%3BHarry%20Potter%26quot%3B-esque%2C%20but%20I%20just%20sat%20back%20and%20watched%20everyone%20else%2C%20and%20that's%20how%20I%20learned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20credit%20Cambridge%20with%20teaching%20me%20how%20to%20engage%20in%20small%20talk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can%20talk%20to%20anyone%20for%20hours%2C%20but%20that%20wasn't%20always%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20skills%20I%20gained%20at%20events%20such%20as%20cocktail%20parties%20at%20Cambridge%20have%20helped%20me%20dine%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20including%20at%20galas%20in%20Dubai%2C%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20and%20the%20residence%20of%20the%20British%20ambassador%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20enjoyed%20teaching%2C%20which%20is%20probably%20why%20I%20started%20my%20etiquette%20business%20after%20decades%20of%20working%20in%20publishing%20and%20wellness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20certified%20online%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fswannschool.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20Swann%20School%20of%20Protocol%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20started%20hosting%20local%20classes.%20I%20now%20live%20in%20Florida%2C%20so%20I%20mainly%20advertise%20through%20Facebook%20groups%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fgroups%2F694490894077952%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EVero%20Beach%20Moms%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Facebook%20ads%2C%20word%20of%20mouth%2C%20and%20local%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%202016%20to%20this%20year%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20ran%20a%20restaurant%20called%20Sealantro%20British%20Cafe%2C%20and%20I%20used%20some%20of%20the%20contacts%20from%20its%20mailing%20list%20to%20grow%20my%20etiquette%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20my%20classes%20with%20children%20and%20expanded%20to%20adults%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20would%20come%20in%20after%20booking%20a%20class%20for%20their%20child%20or%20grandchild%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20do%20something%20about%20my%20husband%3F%26quot%3B%20That's%20a%20very%20common%20theme%2C%20and%20that's%20how%20I%20started%20teaching%20adults.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20now%20teach%20courses%20on%20modern%20formal%20dining%20for%20adults%20and%20college%20students%2C%20dining%20out%20for%20children%2C%20business%20dining%2C%20international%20business%20etiquette%2C%20afternoon-tea%20etiquette%2C%20and%20etiquette%20for%20teenagers.%20They%20range%20from%20%2445%20to%20%24195.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELittle%20ones%20are%20the%20funniest.%20Once%2C%20while%20waiting%20for%20everyone%20to%20be%20served%2C%20one%20little%20boy%20face-planted%20into%20his%20dessert.%20He%20looked%20up%20with%20cream%20and%20strawberry%20shortcake%20over%20his%20face.%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20on%20earth%20did%20you%20do%20that%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20you%20told%20me%20not%20to%20touch%20my%20silverware.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20tell%20me%20they%20feel%20far%20more%20comfortable%20in%20business%20situations%20after%20my%20class%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20lived%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20and%20that%20has%20made%20this%20job%20interesting%20when%20I'm%20teaching%20adults%20who%20travel%20a%20lot.%20There%20are%20nuances%20we%20need%20to%20be%20aware%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20America%2C%20it's%20common%20to%20go%20into%20a%20shop%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20to.%26quot%3B%20In%20many%20other%20countries%2C%20it%20would%20be%20socially%20acceptable%20only%20if%20you%20started%20with%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20have%3F%26quot%3B%20or%2C%20%26quot%3BWould%20you%20mind%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20lived%20in%20the%20Caribbean%2C%20people%20would%20say%20something%20to%20you%20if%20you%20spoke%20like%20that.%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20you%20went%20straight%20into%20asking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20the%20time%3F%26quot%3B%20Someone%20might%20respond%2C%20%26quot%3BGood%20afternoon%2C%20how%20are%20you%20today%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThese%20are%20the%20most%20common%20mistakes%20I%20see%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20dining%2C%20the%20most%20frequent%20mistake%20I%20see%20is%20people%20starting%20to%20eat%20before%20the%20whole%20table%20has%20been%20served.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20include%20leaving%20dirty%20silverware%20on%20the%20table%20instead%20of%20the%20plate%2C%20stabbing%20a%20chunk%20of%20meat%20and%20then%20chewing%20it%20off%20the%20fork%2C%20putting%20elbows%20on%20the%20table%20(seriously%2C%20no%20one%20listened%20to%20Grandma)%2C%20leaning%20over%20the%20plate%20and%20shoveling%20food%2C%20eating%20with%20an%20open%20mouth%2C%20talking%20with%20a%20full%20mouth%2C%20and%20wolfing%20down%20a%20meal%20rather%20than%20following%20the%20pace%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20dining%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20manners%2C%20I%20see%20many%20people%20miss%20the%20basics%2C%20such%20as%20saying%20please%20and%20thank%20you.%20One%20that%20drives%20me%20nuts%20is%20RSVP-ing%20yes%20to%20a%20catered%20event%20and%20then%20not%20showing%20up%20or%20sending%20regrets.%20I've%20seen%20it%20a%20lot%20%E2%80%94%20even%20at%20weddings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20also%20mix%20up%20things%20such%20as%20which%20knife%20to%20use%20for%20butter%20or%20where%20to%20place%20the%20knife%20when%20using%20the%20fork%20in%20the%20American%20style%20(it%20should%20be%20left%20across%20the%20top%20of%20the%20plate%2C%20blade%20facing%20down).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20tell%20my%20American%20clients%2C%20'If%20you%20want%20to%20stand%20out%20when%20you%20travel%2C%20then%20keep%20doing%20what%20you%20are%20doing'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-emily-in-paris-bakery-owner-feels-humiliated-online-criticism-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENetflix's%20%26quot%3BEmily%20in%20Paris%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20good%20example%20of%20this.%20Emily%20can't%20go%20to%20a%20social%20event%20and%20refrain%20from%20discussing%20work%2C%20even%20though%20French%20people%20an