s%20a%20motorbike%20at%20the%20Northstar%20Precision%20Vietnam%20factory%20in%20Vinh%20Phuc%20province.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6502d337992da60019ec1c6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223926%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20worker%20assembles%20a%20motorbike%20in%20Vietnam.%3Cp%3ENhac%20Nguyen%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ESupply%20chains%20are%20diversifying%20away%20from%20China%2C%20causing%20a%20shift%20in%20global-trade%20patterns.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EAnalyses%20of%20trade%20data%20suggest%20Chinese%20manufacturers%20are%20assembling%20fewer%20end%20products%20at%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EInstead%2C%20they're%20shipping%20materials%20and%20intermediate%20products%20to%20Southeast%20Asia%20for%20final%20assembly.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-trade-war-covid-companies-moving-supply-chains-2022-12%5C%22%3ESupply%20chains%20are%20shifting%20away%20from%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20world's%20factory%20floor%20for%20the%20last%20four%20decades%20%E2%80%94%20toward%20other%20low-cost%20manufacturing%20hubs%20in%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20supply%20chains%20got%20messed%20up%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20companies%20were%20already%20considering%20diversifying%20away%20from%20China%20after%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20launched%20a%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Feconomy%2Fchina-economy%2Farticle%2F3146489%2Fus-china-trade-war-timeline-key-dates-and-events-july-2018%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22b395ea199b0825a4787b214170b628c7%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Feconomy%2Fchina-economy%2Farticle%2F3146489%2Fus-china-trade-war-timeline-key-dates-and-events-july-2018%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade%20war%20against%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Tensions%20between%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfr.org%2Ftimeline%2Fus-china-relations%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%2201a03ef179328bd5d277dbbbad58cffb%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfr.org%2Ftimeline%2Fus-china-relations%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%20and%20Beijing%3C%2Fa%3E%20remain%20high%20under%20the%20Biden%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-leaving-china-diversifying-supply-chains-apple-tsmc-mazda-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20including%20Apple%20and%20Mazda%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20moving%20away%20from%20Chinese%20factories%20to%20neighboring%20Asian%20countries%20such%20as%20Vietnam%20and%20Bangladesh%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there's%20more%20to%20that%20than%20meets%20the%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20shows%20that%20while%20manufacturing%20activity%20for%20end%20products%20has%20been%20moving%20out%20of%20China%2C%20supply%20chains%20haven't%20decoupled%20from%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalyses%20of%20trade%20data%20suggest%20Chinese%20manufacturers%20are%20assembling%20fewer%20end%20products%20at%20home.%20Instead%2C%20they%20are%20shipping%20processing%20materials%20and%20intermediate%20products%20to%20Southeast%20Asia%20for%20final%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20are%20moving%20manufacturing%20processes%20to%20other%20countries%2C%20including%20parts%20of%20Asia%20and%20North%20America%2C%20to%20diversify%20their%20supply%20chains.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20they%20are%20demanding%20their%20suppliers%20diversify%20their%20supply%20chains%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Misha%20Govshteyn%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20Houston-based%20company%20MacroFab%2C%20a%20platform%20for%20electronics%20manufacturing%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChina's%20importing%20fewer%20intermediate%20parts%20from%20Asia%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESupply%20chains%20are%20part%20of%20an%20ecosystem.%20To%20produce%20in%20China%2C%20the%20raw%20materials%20or%20intermediate%20parts%20must%20come%20from%20somewhere%20in%20or%20outside%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20moving%20their%20supply%20chains%20out%20of%20China.%20That%20means%20other%20countries%20in%20Asia%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20which%20supply%20commodities%20or%20intermediate%20products%20to%20China%20%E2%80%94%20have%20seen%20their%20exports%20to%20the%20country%20drop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20share%20of%20exports%20from%20Asian%20countries%20has%20fallen%20from%2022%25%20in%20April%202021%20to%2018%25%20in%20June%202023%20based%20on%20their%2012-month%20rolling%20averages%2C%20economists%20from%20Nomura%20Holdings%20wrote%20in%20a%20September%208%20note%20titled%C2%A0%26quot%3BIs%20Asia%20slowly%20decoupling%20from%20China%3F%26quot%3B%20seen%20by%20Insider.%20The%20slowdown%20marks%20the%20biggest%20two-year%20decline%20in%20two%20decades%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20just%20China's%20domestic%20demand%20for%20imports%20that%20have%20fallen%2C%20according%20to%20Nomura's%20analysis%20of%20Chinese%20customs%20data.%20China's%20purchases%20of%20raw%20materials%20and%20intermediate%20products%20from%20most%20other%20Asian%20countries%20have%20fallen%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20particular%2C%20China's%20share%20of%20processing-parts%20exports%20out%20of%20South%20Korea%20and%20Hong%20Kong%20fell%20by%202%25%20over%2026%20months%2C%20from%20April%202021%20through%20June%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENomura%20did%20not%20provide%20absolute%20numbers%20of%20the%20exports%20but%20said%20in%20its%20analysis%20that%20the%20decline%20in%20exports%20of%20processing%20materials%20reflects%20a%20shift%20in%20supply%20chains%20away%20from%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20broader%20trend%20of%20a%20fall%20in%20China's%20share%20in%20Asia's%20overall%20exports%20has%20continued%20for%20some%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Sonal%20Varma%2C%20Nomura's%20chief%20economist%20for%20India%20and%20Asia%20(excluding%20Japan)%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20China's%20share%20in%20Asia%20exports%20has%20been%20falling%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20The%20trend%20is%20shown%20in%20the%20graph%20below%20where%20the%20dotted%20line%20represents%20a%20general%20trendline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22432%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Asian%20exports%20to%20China%20has%20been%20falling%20for%20years.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65041490956dba001ace0c96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22349%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAsian%20exports%20to%20China%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20total%20exports%20have%20been%20falling%20in%20recent%20years.%3Cp%3ENomura%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EChina's%20exports%20to%20Southeast%20Asia%20for%20product%20assembly%20have%20risen%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20Asia%20may%20appear%20to%20be%20decoupling%20from%20China%2C%20at%20least%20one%20region%20on%20the%20continent%20is%20getting%20more%20tied%20up%20with%20the%20East%20Asian%20giant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoutheast%20Asian%20trade%20with%20the%20East%20Asian%20giant%20has%20gotten%20more%20intertwined%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2023%2F02%2Ffriendshoring-global-trade-buzzwords%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20phenomenon%20called%20friendshoring%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20practice%20where%20supply%20chains%20are%20focused%20on%20countries%20considered%20to%20be%20political%20or%20economic%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20report%20from%20HSBC%20released%20in%20September%20showed%20that%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-09-05%2Fchina-s-largest-export-market-is-now-much-closer-to-home%5C%22%3EChinese%20exports%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20going%20to%20Southeast%20Asia%20than%20the%20US%20and%20Europe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExports%20from%20China%20to%20the%2010-member%20Association%20of%20Southeast%20Asian%20Nations%20have%20reached%20nearly%20%24600%20billion%20a%20month%20based%20on%2012-month%20moving%20averages%20compiled%20by%20the%20bank%20%E2%80%94%20surpassing%20the%20bloc's%20shipments%20to%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20since%20earlier%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20is%20partly%20because%20parts%20sourced%20from%20China%20are%20getting%20shipped%20to%20Southeast%20Asia%20for%20final%20assembly%20before%20getting%20reexported%20to%20their%20final%20consumer%20destinations%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20wrote%20Frederic%20Neumann%2C%20the%20chief%20Asia%20economist%20for%20HSBC%2C%20in%20the%20report%20seen%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHSBC's%20observations%20echo%20findings%20made%20in%20an%20April%20report%20by%20Yukon%20Huang%20and%20Genevieve%20Slosberg%2C%20researchers%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2F2023%2F04%2F11%2Fwhat-exactly-does-washington-want-from-its-trade-war-with-beijing-pub-89503%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECarnegie%20Asia%20Program.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20found%20that%20China%20played%20a%20%26quot%3Bbehind-the-scene%26quot%3B%20role%20in%20supplying%20components%20and%20materials%20for%20other%20countries'%20exports%20to%20the%20US%2C%20even%20though%20China's%20share%20of%20total%20goods%20imported%20into%20America%20fell%20from%2022%25%20to%2017%25%20between%202017%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20may%20be%20exporting%20less%20to%20the%20United%20States%20directly%2C%20but%20it%20is%20now%20indirectly%20exporting%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Insider%20reported%20in%20April%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-supply-chains-moving-companies-outside-mainland-2023-4%5C%22%3Eeven%20Chinese%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0are%20moving%20their%20supply%20chains%20out%20of%20China%20to%20avoid%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20US%20companies%20had%20specifically%20asked%20Guangdong%20Vanward%20New%20Electric%2C%20China's%20largest%20water-heater%20maker%2C%20to%20build%20factories%20outside%20the%20country%20%26quot%3Bto%20continue%20co-operation%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Lu%20Yucong%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20Guangdong%20Vanward%20New%20Electric%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fdaf7392e-1850-4bdb-bb74-b310e87f0727%3F__cf_chl_rt_tk%3Dg7D9PSY.6HrTrtDhTr8bJcORda2e.kJGnOyzDXb9_GA-1695114021-0-gaNycGzNDKU%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Times%20in%20April.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChina%20will%20likely%20continue%20to%20play%20a%20big%20part%20of%20the%20world's%20supply%20chains%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20rhetoric%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-derisking-decoupling-difference-strategy-definition-wef-2023-6%5C%22%3Ede-risking%20away%20from%20China%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20world's%20second-largest%20economy%20is%20likely%20to%20continue%20playing%20an%20outsize%20role%20in%20global%20trade%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20indirectly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20China%20accounted%20for%20about%20one-third%20of%20the%20world's%20total%20manufacturing%20output%2C%20according%20to%20Carnegie's%20Huang%20and%20Slosberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaroFab's%20Govshteyn%20echoed%20the%20sentiment%3A%20%26quot%3BChina%20will%20always%20be%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20global%20trade%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrad